@everyone Alright, this announcement is for the debate. I'll be doing mine at 2:00 PM EDT, 1:00 CDT, 11:00 AM PDT. Which is US Time. @Frank will be doing EU Time, at 17-18 UTC. This will be a simple debate, we'll vote for a topic to bring to the senate on Wednesday. Where you'll vote for said topic to go which ever way. The Speaker will have five minutes, afterwards anyone who wishes to refute has three minutes to do so. Topics of Debate: Position Of Military Leader- As the military lead head of Patrium has sadly passed away, the High Court wants to nominate a person of interest as possible candidate. This is more of to show you candidate, and explain why they are the best option as the new head of the Armed Forces. Or you can also debate the topic of Military leaders or propose a different way of doing things. Parties will nominate a person to create a character, it doesn't have to be very long. Economic Policy- Patrium has fallen on hard times, the economy is dangling on a thread. Give your stance on how you plan to fix the economy. Such how you'll stabilize the currency, and manage the Federal Debt. Adam's Centrism: This prompt will about the current President, Adam, and his neutral stance on most matters. You'll give your stance on his neutral ways, and party opinion of him. Like I said, we'll vote for a Topic at the end. Then do a senate-vote on Wednesday.

Deleted User 14-May-20 08:52 AM
@everyone As news of the military's delegitimization of the Senate spread across the country, chaos erupted in the streets. What were once peaceful towns and villages became centers of violence and destruction. As stability continued to break down, the guards in the President's palace urgently rushed to Adams' quarters to inform him of the news. They bursted into his room, hoping that he would bring order to the noise and chaos of Patrium. But when they called out his name...they could only hear the echo of their own voices bouncing off the walls of the large, barren room. Their eyes crawled along the walls of the chamber until they finally reached the President's bed. In the darkness, they could make out what seemed to be the silhouette of a thin, fragile, man laying motionless on the mattress. Thinking that Adams was asleep, they rushed over to his bedside and begged him to awaken, but there would be no response. His eyes were wide open, staring blankly into the ceiling above him. His body, totally still, as if he was a mannequin on display. The guard reached out with his short, stubby fingers and clasped the wrist of the President. It was as cold and lifeless as stone. The guard's eyes widened and his face quickly twisted into a frightened knot as he whispered, "The President is dead...."

Things have not been going well in Patrium’s newly annexed territory, the Provisional Acquisition Region (PAR). Acquired from Thuzland in the peace deal following the Nuevo Brabante War (dubbed by many Patrians as the War of Thuzi Aggression), the area is full of Thuzis who now suddenly find themselves a part of Patrium. Protests against the military occupation are still rampant in most cities, and some have devolved into riots. The military is still working to subdue these, and while it has been largely successful, there have been Thuzi fatalities numbering in the dozens. Many Thuzis have attempted to flee back across the new border, but are currently being stopped by the Patrian military. While local Thuzi governments are still in place, no overarching government exists besides the tenuous hold of military command, and much of the PAR’s infrastructure has begun to fall apart.
Your Task: The senate has been tasked with creating a plan on what to do with the PAR. The bill should include a plan for the citizenship status, rights, and privileges of the Thuzis in the PAR, as well as the region’s new government structure and status; any measures to be taken toward the integration of the Thuzis into Patrium; and if/how you will deal with the riots; a budget allocation for reconstruction of infrastructure (more information forthcoming); as well as any other measures you see fit to include. Additionally, President Taylor has decided to create the position of Provisional Overseer, to be filled by a senator. The Provisional Overseer will oversee the implementation of the measures included in the bill, as well as act as a go-between for the senate, the president, and the military and leadership in the PAR. The Provisional Governor will be elected by the senate. Finally, in order to smooth the transition for the PAR, a delegation of senators will be sent to a host a public convention in the PAR, to meet with local Thuzi leaders, as well as our generals in the area, and make speeches to the public. This delegation will be open to any senator who wishes to go. The event will be held in Philipstown, and more details about its structure will be forthcoming. The event in Philipstown will be Sunday at 20:00 UTC/4:00 pm est, and the debate, nominations, and voting will follow in subsequent days. (edited)
